						<summary>

						<p>The inscription states that this spring (well) is the gift of Iṟaṅgalmīṭṭa Tāḻaiyūr-Nāḍāḻvāṉ, son of Araiśuviṟṟirundāṉ Iḷaiyaraiyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Iḍaiyāṟṟūr-Nāḍāḻvān who had the <hi rend="italic">kāval</hi> right over Tiruttavattuṟai in Iḍaiyāṟṟūr-nāḍu a division of Pāṇḍikulāśani-vaḷanāḍu. This place is evidently the same as the present Lālguḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
